verbose_text: Our results showed G6PD A- allele could significantly reduce the risk of Plasmodium falciparum infection in male individuals (adjusted odds ratio [AOR], 0.43; 95% confidence interval [CI], 0.20-0.93; p <.05) and homozygous female individuals (AOR, 0.11; 95% CI, 0.01-0.84; p <.05).
